						               													<description>User summary:&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#181;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#142;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160; (Sainome Colosseum) is a card game where two fantasy characters fight each other. The publisher MR &amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#191;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#134;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136; (MR Entertainment) is the designer for this game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, you may perform two of the following actions:&amp;#10;1) Fill your hand up to five cards&amp;#10;2) Equip yourself with cards in your hand and/or currently equipped cards&amp;#10;3) Play a card for a special effect&amp;#10;4) Attack your opponent&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You have four slots to equip weapons, spells and/or items. In general, weak cards are versatile and can be equipped on any slot, but strong ones must be equipped on a certain slot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When attacking, you roll a die to determine which slot is activated (roll of a 2 activates slot A, a 3 activates slot B, etc.), then damage and effect are determined. Used cards are discarded, so you will have to refill the slot, or your chance of a miss will be increased on your next attack.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each character has their own special ability that goes well with specific cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win the game when your opponent's life is reduced to zero.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Publisher's summary:&amp;#10;2&amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#148;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#229;&amp;#175;&amp;#190;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#166;&amp;#229;&amp;#158;&amp;#139;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&